g.text: ProfileClass is an example of AnyEntityClass
SpecClass is an example of AnyEntityClass
i.e. a spec can have a spec
SpecClass provides capability to express ranges of values and value range interrelationships. A
value range interrelationship may state that if one attribute takes a specific value of its range
another attribute must take a specific value of its range.
This capability is applied such that an attribute specified in a specific AnyEntityClass which the
specific SpecInstance abides by can be constrained so as to be a narrowed definition of the
attribute with respect to that provided in the specific AnyEntityClass.
The SpecInstance abides by the specific AnyEntityClass in that it can only constrain attributes
that are valid in that specific AnyEntiyClass.
Each AnyEntityInstance must reference a SpecInstance. A specific SpecInstance can be
referenced by a specific AnyEntityInstance that conforms to the specific AnyEntityClass that
The effect of the reference is to constrain each attribute of the AnyEntityInstance as defined in
the SpecInstance. Only attributes stated in the SpecInstance are available and relevant to each
The SpecInstance always narrows definitions so for example it may change a attribute to
ReadOnly from read/write but it may not do the reverse and it may narrow an integer range
but not change an integer to a string.
If the AnyEntityClass has a freeform NVSPList the SpecInstance may provide specific legal
values for strings of the list effectively adding attributes but only by the narrowing of a
The ProfileInstance works in a very similar way accept that it must also abide by the
SpecInstance that the specific AnyEntityInstance references and that if it does not state an
attribute then it has no affect on the attribute which continues as defined in the SpecInstance.
